    public class ContextEditor
extends KSJInternalFrame
    The ContextEditor is a window that displays some of a Context's fields for user editing. It is an extension of KSJInternalFrame because I want this to appear in the View menu.

    The ContextEditor can only display one context - the current Library.contextUnderConstruction. Often there will be only one; if there are more, the User must choose one to be his current focus, then edit it.
